============
Description:
============ 
@timeout decorator to stop executing functions


======
Usage:
======
# import the module
from timeout import timeout


# add the decorator, and voil√†!
@timeout(5)
def my_function():
    ...


# it may be defined a callback, like this:


def my_callback():
    print 'finished by timeout'


@timeout(period=5, callback=my_callback) 
def my_function():
    ...

